## ‚úçÔ∏è CONTENT CREATION GUIDELINES

### ADVANCED KEYWORD STRATEGY (Blog Generator Inspired)

**Keyword Density & Natural Integration:**

**Primary Keyword Usage:**
- ‚úÖ H1 heading (once, naturally)
- ‚úÖ First 100 words of introduction
- ‚úÖ First H2 section heading
- ‚úÖ Hero image alt text
- ‚úÖ 2-3 content images alt text
- ‚úÖ URL slug
- ‚úÖ Meta description (150-160 chars)
- ‚ö†Ô∏è Total mentions: Natural flow, NOT forced count
- üéØ Philosophy: Satisfy search intent > hit density percentage

**Cluster Keywords Distribution:**
- Scatter throughout H2/H3 headings (40% of headings should contain cluster terms)
- Use in subheadings naturally
- Integrate into callout boxes
- Include in image alt text (vary across images)
- Minimum 5-8 different cluster keywords used
- Each cluster keyword appears 2-4 times naturally

**Semantic/LSI Keywords:**
- Use in body paragraphs for context
- Support primary keyword meaning
- Help AI understand topic comprehensively
- Include synonyms and related concepts
- Target: 15-20 unique semantic terms throughout page

**Long-Tail Keyword Integration:**
- Use as H3 subheadings (question format)
- Answer directly in following paragraph
- Each long-tail = one image alt text
- Include in FAQ questions
- Target voice search queries

**Topical Authority Signals:**
- Cover related subtopics comprehensively
- Link to semantically related internal pages
- Use entity-based language (proper nouns, brands, techniques)
- Include co-occurring terms found in top SERP results

**Natural Keyword Integration Pattern:**
```
‚ùå BAD (Forced):
"Nail care is important. Nail care helps nails. For nail care, use nail care products."

‚úÖ GOOD (Natural):
"Proper nail maintenance keeps your nails healthy and strong. Using quality cuticle oil 
and gentle filing techniques makes a noticeable difference. These simple practices 
prevent breakage and promote natural growth."
```

**AVOID:**
- ‚ùå Keyword stuffing (unnatural repetition)
- ‚ùå Exact match overuse (vary phrasing)
- ‚ùå Forcing keywords into every paragraph
- ‚ùå Sacrificing readability for SEO
- ‚ùå Generic anchor text for internal links

---

### IMAGE SEO STRATEGY (Advanced)

**Filename Optimization:**
```
Format: [topic-slug]-[descriptive-keyword]-[number].webp

‚úÖ GOOD Examples:
- nail-care-guide-cuticle-oil-application.webp
- skin-tones-warm-undertone-test.webp
- seasonal-trends-winter-2025-colors.webp

‚ùå BAD Examples:
- image1.jpg
- IMG_0023.jpg
- nail_care.png (underscores)
```

**Filename Rules:**
1. Lowercase only
2. Hyphens (not underscores)
3. Include 1-2 relevant keywords
4. Descriptive of image content
5. Unique across all images (no duplicates)
6. 3-6 words maximum
7. No special characters

**Alt Text Formula:**
```
Format: [Long-tail keyword] + [specific context] (under 125 characters)

Hero Image Alt:
"[Primary keyword] [user intent phrase]"
Example: "Complete nail care guide featuring essential tools and techniques for healthy nails"

Content Images Alt (MUST BE UNIQUE):
Image 1: "Step-by-step cuticle care routine with oil application for beginners"
Image 2: "Best nail strengthening products recommended by professionals"
Image 3: "Common nail problems and solutions illustrated guide"
Image 4: "Proper nail filing technique demonstrated on natural nails"
```

**Alt Text Rules:**
- ‚úÖ Start directly with description (NO "image of" prefix)
- ‚úÖ Under 125 characters strict
- ‚úÖ Include unique long-tail keyword per image
- ‚úÖ Describe what's actually visible
- ‚úÖ Voice search friendly (conversational)
- ‚úÖ Context-relevant to surrounding text
- ‚ùå Never repeat alt text across images
- ‚ùå No keyword stuffing

**Image Gallery Strategy:**
- First 3 content images = featured gallery (schema)
- Each image targets different long-tail variation
- Alt text uses semantic keywords from research
- Filenames incorporate cluster keywords
- Varied terminology across all images

**Technical Specs:**
- Hero: 1200x630px, WebP/JPG, <100KB
- Content: 1200x800px, WebP/JPG, <80KB each
- Lazy loading: `loading="lazy"` on all below-fold
- Responsive: Include width/height attributes

---

### Structure Template (All Topics)

**1. Hero Section (Above Fold)**
- Gradient background with topic-relevant image
- H1 with power words + primary keyword (naturally integrated)
- Subheading (value proposition, benefits)
- Scroll indicator animation
- Estimated read time badge
- Quick stats badge (e.g., "12,000+ readers")

**2. Quick Stats/Facts Bar**
- 3-4 compelling statistics in glass cards
- Icons for visual interest
- Sources cited below (external authority links)
- Animated counters on scroll

**3. Table of Contents (Sticky)**
- Jump links to H2 sections
- Progress indicator (% read)
- "Back to top" functionality
- Collapses on mobile, sticky on desktop

**4. Introduction Section**
- Hook (surprising statistic or question)
- Primary keyword in first 100 words
- What readers will learn (bullet points)
- Credibility statement (E-E-A-T signal)
- Internal link to related content
- Length: 200-250 words

**5. Main Content Sections (Modular)**
Each H2 section includes:
- Numbered heading with emoji icon + cluster keyword
- 2-3 paragraph intro (2-3 sentences per paragraph)
- Visual element (image with proper SEO)
- H3 subsections with long-tail keywords
- Callout box (pro tip/warning/scientific fact)
- Internal link naturally integrated
- Horizontal rule separator (---) between sections

**Image Frequency:** Every 200-300 words

**6. FAQ Section (Structured)**
- Minimum 10 questions (from voice search research)
- Accordion format (expand/collapse)
- Questions = exact long-tail keywords users search
- Answers = 40-60 words (direct + explanation + tip)
- No apostrophes in questions/answers (schema compatibility)

**7. E-E-A-T Section**
- Position: After FAQ, before Related Topics
- Heading: "## About Mirell√© Team"
- Content: 3 lines maximum describing expertise
- Link to /about page
- Example: "We're nail enthusiasts who test and curate designs from artists worldwide. Our mission is bringing you trend-forward inspiration that's actually achievable. <a href='/about' class='text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline'>Learn more about us</a>."

**8. Related Topics (Internal Linking)**
- 3 linked topic cards with images
- Brief descriptions (50-75 words)
- "Read more" CTAs
- Grid layout with hover effects

**9. Newsletter CTA**
- Inline (not popup)
- Value proposition clear ("Get weekly nail trends")
- Single field (email)
- Privacy assurance
- Glass card design

---

### Content Quality Standards

**Word Count by Topic:**
- Nail Care Guide: 3,500-4,500 words (competitors average 3,000)
- Nail Art Guides: 3,000-3,800 words (competitors average 2,500)
- Seasonal Trends: 2,500-3,200 words (competitors average 2,200)
- Modern Women: 2,800-3,500 words (competitors average 2,400)
- At-Home Hacks: 2,500-3,200 words (competitors average 2,100)
- Skin Tones: 3,000-3,800 words (competitors average 2,600)

**Target: 15-25% above competitor average**

**Readability Standards:**
- Flesch Reading Ease: 60-70 (8th-9th grade)
- Average sentence length: 15-20 words
- Paragraph length: 2-3 sentences max (mobile-friendly)
- Transition words: 30%+ of sentences
- Active voice: 80%+ of sentences
- Vary sentence length (mix short & medium)

**Paragraph Structure:**
- ‚úÖ One idea per paragraph
- ‚úÖ Transition words between paragraphs
- ‚úÖ Short sentences for mobile readability
- ‚úÖ Use conversational tone (not robotic)
- ‚úÖ Break complex ideas into steps

**Engagement Elements (Per 500 Words):**
- 1-2 images/visuals (with SEO alt text)
- 1 callout box (colored background, icon)
- 1 internal link (varied anchor text)
- 1 list (bulleted/numbered)

**Voice Search Optimization:**
- Write H2/H3 as questions users ask
- Answer question in first sentence of section
- Use conversational phrasing
- Include "how to", "what is", "best way to" patterns
- FAQ section targets exact voice queries

**Internal Linking Strategy:**
- Minimum 5 internal links per topic page
- Link to: Parent topic (1), related topics (2-3), blog posts (1-2)
- Anchor text variations:
  - Exact match keyword (1 time)
  - Partial match (2-3 times)
  - Branded/natural (1-2 times)
- Link placement: Naturally within content flow
- Open in same tab (not new window)
- Use Tailwind classes: `class='text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline'`

**External Authority Linking:**
- Minimum 3-4 authority sources
- Link to: Studies, brand websites, industry leaders, medical sources
- Use for: Supporting claims, statistics, product info, dermatology facts
- Always open in new tab: `target='_blank' rel='noopener'`
- Cite naturally in content: "According to a 2024 study by [Source]..."

**E-E-A-T Signals Throughout:**
- Cite specific studies with years
- Reference expert techniques ("dermatologists recommend...")
- Show testing/experience ("we tested 15 products over 30 days")
- Include statistics from research
- Update dates visible ("Updated: November 2025")
- Author credibility statement

